sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant Agent as OpenClaw Agent
    participant Plugin as SafeClaw Plugin<br/>(TypeScript)
    participant API as SafeClaw API<br/>(FastAPI)
    participant Engine as FullEngine
    participant KG as Knowledge Graph<br/>(RDFLib + OWL)
    participant SHACL as SHACL Validator<br/>(pySHACL)
    participant Audit as Audit Logger<br/>(JSONL)

    Note over Agent,Audit: SESSION START

    Agent->>Plugin: before_agent_start event
    Plugin->>API: POST /api/v1/context/build
    API->>Engine: build_context(session, user)
    Engine->>KG: Query user preferences
    KG-->>Engine: Preferences (OWL triples)
    Engine->>KG: Query active policies
    KG-->>Engine: Policies (prohibitions, obligations)
    Engine->>KG: Query session facts
    KG-->>Engine: Session state
    Engine-->>API: ContextResult (governance prompt)
    API-->>Plugin: { prependContext: "## SafeClaw Governance..." }
    Plugin-->>Agent: Inject constraints into system prompt

    Note over Agent,Audit: TOOL CALL EVALUATION

    Agent->>Plugin: before_tool_call(toolName, params)
    Plugin->>API: POST /api/v1/evaluate/tool-call
    API->>Engine: evaluate_tool_call(event)

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Engine: Step 0: Agent Governance
        Engine->>Engine: Verify agent token
        Engine->>Engine: Check kill switch
        Engine->>Engine: Detect delegation bypass
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Engine,KG: Step 1: Action Classification
        Engine->>KG: Classify tool + params → OWL action class
        KG-->>Engine: ActionClass (risk, reversibility, scope)
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Engine,KG: Step 2: Role-Based Access
        Engine->>KG: Check agent role vs action class
        KG-->>Engine: Role permission result
    end

    rect rgb(255, 250, 230)
        Note over Engine,SHACL: Step 3: SHACL Validation
        Engine->>SHACL: Validate action graph against shapes
        SHACL-->>Engine: Conforms / Violation report
    end

    alt SHACL violation detected
        Engine->>Audit: Log BLOCKED decision
        Audit-->>Engine: Audit ID
        Engine-->>API: Decision: BLOCKED (SHACL violation)
        API-->>Plugin: { block: true, reason: "..." }
        Plugin-->>Agent: Action blocked with explanation
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Engine,KG: Step 4: Policy Check
        Engine->>KG: SPARQL query for matching prohibitions
        KG-->>Engine: Matching policies (if any)
    end

    alt Policy prohibition matched
        Engine->>Audit: Log BLOCKED decision
        Engine-->>API: Decision: BLOCKED (policy violation)
        API-->>Plugin: { block: true, reason: "..." }
        Plugin-->>Agent: Action blocked with explanation
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Engine,KG: Step 5: Preference Check
        Engine->>KG: Query user preferences for action type
        KG-->>Engine: Preference constraints
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Engine: Step 6: Dependency Check
        Engine->>Engine: Check session history for prerequisites
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Engine: Step 7: Temporal & Rate Limit
        Engine->>Engine: Check time constraints
        Engine->>Engine: Check rate limits
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Engine: Step 8: Derived Rules
        Engine->>Engine: Evaluate combined OWL inferences
    end

    Note over Engine: All 9 steps passed

    Engine->>Engine: Record action for rate limiting
    Engine->>Audit: Log ALLOWED decision
    Audit-->>Engine: Audit ID
    Engine-->>API: Decision: ALLOWED
    API-->>Plugin: { block: false }
    Plugin-->>Agent: Action permitted — proceed

    Note over Agent,Audit: TOOL RESULT FEEDBACK

    Agent->>Plugin: after_tool_call(result)
    Plugin->>API: POST /api/v1/record/tool-result
    API->>Engine: record_action_result(event)
    Engine->>KG: Update session facts (outcome, state changes)
    KG-->>Engine: Facts stored
    Engine-->>API: OK
    API-->>Plugin: 200 OK

    Note over Agent,Audit: MESSAGE GOVERNANCE

    Agent->>Plugin: message_sending(to, content)
    Plugin->>API: POST /api/v1/evaluate/message
    API->>Engine: evaluate_message(event)
    Engine->>KG: Check communication policies
    KG-->>Engine: Policy result
    Engine->>Audit: Log message decision
    Engine-->>API: Decision: ALLOWED / BLOCKED
    API-->>Plugin: { cancel: false } or { cancel: true, reason: "..." }
    Plugin-->>Agent: Send or cancel message
